5|$|A {{new record}} of 195 million viewers for the Eurovision Song Contest was reported. The {{official}} compilation {{album of the}} 2014 Contest was released by Universal Music Group on 14 April 2014, and featured all 37 songs from the contest, including the official #JoinUs theme performed during the interval act of the grand final. The <b>host</b> <b>broadcaster,</b> DR, and the EBU won the International TV Award at the Ondas Awards for their production of the contest.|$|E
5|$|As {{part of the}} contest's graphic design, special postcards were {{commissioned}} by the Danish <b>host</b> <b>broadcaster</b> DR to introduce each of the participating countries before the acts took to the stage. For the 2014 contest the contestants were asked to take a photo of their country's flag, made in a creative way. Austria's postcard {{was the first to}} be filmed by DR, and was shot at the Schönbrunn Palace in Vienna featuring Wurst and her stylist Tamara Mascara creating the Austrian flag out of 70 baroque-style dresses.|$|E
